subhed: In France, a growing share of the population is struggling to find housing. The shortage, which especially affects the working and middle classes, is generating resentment with consequences at the ballot box.

title: Germany pushes ahead to become Europe's leading space power
subhed: Member states of the European Space Agency, meeting in Bremen, approved a €22.1 billion budget for 2026-2028 – a 32% increase. Germany will contribute €5.1 billion, or 23% of the funds, taking on a leadership role in Europe's space program.
